# Stage 1: Chef - Plan Rust dependencies
FROM rust:1.78 AS chef
RUN cargo install cargo-chef
WORKDIR /app

# Stage 2: Rust Builder - Build Rust binary
FROM chef AS rust-builder
COPY server/Cargo.toml server/Cargo.lock ./
RUN cargo chef prepare --recipe-path recipe.json
RUN cargo chef cook --release --recipe-path recipe.json
COPY server/src ./src
RUN cargo build --release
RUN mv target/release/inference-server /usr/local/bin/inference-server

# Stage 3: Python Builder - Build Python environment
FROM python:3.11-slim-bookworm AS python-builder
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    build-essential \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
RUN python -m venv /opt/venv
ENV PATH="/opt/venv/bin:$PATH"
RUN pip install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir \
    torch==2.1.2 --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu \
    transformers==4.36.2 \
    tokenizers==0.14.1 \
    safetensors==0.4.1

# Stage 4: Runtime - Final minimal image
FROM debian:bookworm-slim
LABEL maintainer="inference-server"
LABEL description="Rust + Python ML Inference Server"
LABEL version="1.0"

RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    ca-certificates \
    curl \
    libssl3 \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

RUN groupadd -r inference && useradd -r -u 1000 -g inference inference

COPY --from=rust-builder /usr/local/bin/inference-server /usr/local/bin/inference-server
COPY --from=python-builder /opt/venv /opt/venv

ENV PATH="/opt/venv/bin:$PATH"
ENV PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1

WORKDIR /app
RUN chown -R inference:inference /app

USER inference

EXPOSE 8080

HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=10s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \
    CMD curl -f http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1

ENTRYPOINT ["/usr/local/bin/inference-server", "--port", "8080"]
